prompts.text:
Use case: identity-preserve.
Asset type: grid-safe clean-source regeneration of a production 2D overworld NPC true-eight-direction static idle sheet for Beastbound Odyssey.

The first supplied image, the healer identity board, is the exact identity authority. The second supplied image is a rejected otherwise-useful true-eight reference: its first-row feet cross the exact 50% horizontal grid boundary. Regenerate the complete sheet as new independently authored pixels. Preserve the identity and direction semantics, but do not edit, trace, copy pixel-for-pixel, or preserve any boundary-crossing pixels from the rejected sheet.

Create an exact 2-row by 4-column sheet of the same original mature female village healer in eight independently authored static idle directions. She is approximately 50, medium height and softly sturdy, with warm-brown skin, hazel-brown eyes and gentle eye-corner lines. Her silver-gray long braid stays coiled in a low side bun on her own RIGHT rear side. She wears a rounded sage-green short shoulder cape, layered village tunic, ivory scarf, pale sky-blue cloth bindings, herb-brown trousers, belt and boots. A sealed corked herb tube always rests in her own LEFT arm; a closed mortar pouch remains at her own RIGHT waist; a slim closed bone-needle case remains at the back belt. All containers stay closed and close to the body.

Exact row-major screen-facing order:
row 1 south = exact front facing down-screen;
southwest = front-left with nose, chest, knees and toes toward the LEFT edge;
west = pure left profile;
northwest = back-left with back dominant and axis toward upper-left.
row 2 north = exact complete back with no face or eye and a vertical up-screen axis;
northeast = back-right with back dominant and axis toward upper-right;
east = pure right profile;
southeast = front-right with nose, chest, knees and toes toward the RIGHT edge.
Opposite diagonals must expose opposite shoulders. Every direction is independently authored; no mirroring, duplication, rotation, relabeling or reuse.

The sheet must be an exact invisible 2x4 grid. The full-canvas horizontal row boundary is exactly at 50% height. Reserve a completely empty flat-magenta safety band from 44% through 56% of the full canvas: no top-row foot, boot, outline or antialiasing may extend below 44%, and no bottom-row hair, head, outline or antialiasing may rise above 56%. Place every top-row full body only within full-canvas y=4%-43% and every bottom-row full body only within y=57%-96%. Make all eight bodies the same height and feet baseline within their row.

Within each of the four equal-width columns, keep the complete character inside the central 56% of that cell and leave at least 18% uninterrupted flat-magenta padding at both the left and right cell boundaries. Nothing may touch or cross the vertical boundaries at 25%, 50% or 75% of full-canvas width. There must be exactly one connected character per cell and no detached line, dot, colored residue, loose prop or neighboring-cell fragment. No borders, labels, dividers, text, arrows, UI or watermark.

The entire background must be perfectly uniform, fully opaque, flat exact #FF00FF with a crisp hard boundary around the subject: no gradient, texture, floor, reflection, contact shadow, cast shadow, checkerboard, glow or halo. Reserve magenta exclusively for the removable background. Do not use magenta, hot pink, rose-purple, purple or violet anywhere in skin, hair, eyes, lips, hands, clothing, bindings, outlines, shadows, antialiasing, herb tube, pouch, needle case or other props. Keep the healer palette strictly sage green, ivory, pale sky blue, herb brown, silver gray and natural warm skin tones.

Clean original Beastbound Odyssey hand-painted HD 2D sprite art with warm outlines and controlled cel shading. No scenery, animal, second person, modern medical device, nurse cap, medical cross, open liquid, magic staff, religious symbol, particles, glow, halo or StoneAge source art.
